### Set Up

Once Youve imported the code you will need to set a command such as `!uptime` to the `UpTime` Action. Then you can do the next step 1 of 2 ways, 1 you can tie the OBS Event of Starting and Ending stream to the 2 remaining actions accordingly. However you may already have an action that does actions when you start streaming, in that case you can just copy and paste the C# and Set Globals Sub Actions into those already created actions.

### Variables Avaliable
In the output message you can put the following variables and for `1 hour 30 mins and 20 secs` they will output as follows
- `%uptime.secs%` = 20
- `%uptime.mins%` = 30
- `%uptime.hours%` = 1
- `%uptime.days%` = 0
- `%uptime.totalsecs%` = 5420
- `%uptime.totalmins%` = 90
- `%uptime.totalhours%`  = 1
- `%uptime.totaldays%` = 0
